&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Are you passionate about solving complex challenges in the fintech space? We’re looking for talented individuals to join our dynamic startup, backed by Sequoia Capital. We’re building the universal payment layer to unify all currencies—fiat and crypto—so businesses and consumers can transact seamlessly. If you&#39;re passionate about creating innovative solutions in a dynamic, fast-paced environment, we want to talk to you.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are hiring a FinOps &amp;amp; Accounting Analyst!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a high-ownership, high-breadth role sitting at the heart of Breeze’s Finance &amp;amp; Operations function. You’ll work directly alongside the Finance Lead, touching everything from accounting and treasury to merchant operations and compliance support. This is a hands-on opportunity to learn how a real payments business runs from the inside — and to have meaningful impact from day one at a fast-moving, Sequoia-backed startup.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review the bookkeeper’s work for accuracy; prepare and post ad-hoc journal entries and coding corrections&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run weekly BigQuery queries to generate revenue data and import results to QuickBooks Online (QBO)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle chargeback close entries, prepaid amortization schedules, and month-end close support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run weekly cash reconciliations across all accounts and entities; maintain cash position reports and monitor liquidity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process vendor invoices through Bill.com on a twice-weekly cycle; review and categorize expenses in Ramp&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Issue merchant invoices, chase late payments, and field vendor payment queries from internal teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calculate and process referral fee payments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond to merchant queries on charges, balance reconciliations, top-up amounts, and tax collected&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support merchant onboarding by verifying bank details and settlement information&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Investigate settlement discrepancies and coordinate with payment partners on resolution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pull documentation and data for KYB, compliance, and due diligence requests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review Numeral sales tax filings for accuracy; manage state-specific follow-ups&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support MTL (Money Transmission License) applications — pulling documentation, responding to state regulator requests, and tracking status&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform monthly and quarterly filing checks; send merchant settlement completion notifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of relevant experience in accounting, finance, or operations — ideally in fintech, payments, or a fast-paced startup&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail — you catch things others miss and take ownership of getting them right&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working with spreadsheets and data; SQL or BigQuery experience is a plus (or a genuine drive to learn)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with QBO, Bill.com, or Ramp is a bonus, not a requirement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You don’t need hand-holding to figure things out — you ask when stuck, but you try first&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills for handling merchant queries and cross-functional coordination&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in payments, fintech, or financial infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Accounting, Finance, Business, or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Culture&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fast-paced and dynamic – &lt;/strong&gt;We’re a growing startup that moves quickly and values people who can keep up&lt

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Are you passionate about solving complex challenges in the fintech space? We’re looking for talented individuals to join our dynamic startup, backed by Sequoia Capital. We’re building the universal payment layer to unify all currencies—fiat and crypto—so businesses and consumers can transact seamlessly. If you&#39;re passionate about creating innovative solutions in a dynamic, fast-paced environment, we want to talk to you.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are hiring a Recruiter&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you passionate about building exceptional teams in the fintech space? We’re looking for a Recruiter to join our dynamic startup, backed by Sequoia Capital. We’re building the universal payment layer to unify all currencies - fiat and crypto - so businesses and consumers can transact seamlessly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you’ll own full-cycle recruiting across multiple functions, with a strong focus on outbound sourcing and talent engagement. You’ll help scale high-performing teams across sales, operations, and technical functions, partnering closely with hiring managers to identify and attract top talent. This is a highly hands-on role where creativity, persistence, and relationship-building are critical to success. If you thrive in fast-paced startup environments and enjoy finding exceptional talent before anyone else does, we’d love to chat.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outbound sourcing - Proactively identify, engage, and build relationships with top-tier candidates across sales, technical, and business functions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full-cycle recruiting - Manage the recruiting process end-to-end from sourcing and screening through offer and closing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sales hiring - Lead recruiting efforts for GTM functions including BDRs, AEs, partnerships, and sales leadership roles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical support - Assist with recruiting for engineering, product, and technical infrastructure roles as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pipeline development - Build and maintain strong candidate pipelines for current and future hiring needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Candidate experience - Deliver a high-quality, responsive, and thoughtful experience throughout the interview process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stakeholder partnership - Work closely with hiring managers and leadership to align on hiring needs, interview processes, and talent strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process improvement - Help refine recruiting operations, sourcing strategies, interview coordination, and hiring workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Market intelligence - Stay informed on talent trends, compensation benchmarks, and competitive hiring landscapes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employer branding - Represent Breeze externally and help position the company as a top destination for talent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in full-cycle recruiting with strong outbound sourcing capabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience hiring for sales and go-to-market roles is required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to support technical recruiting efforts across engineering and product teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong sourcing skills across LinkedIn, recruiting platforms, referrals, and creative outbound strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and relationship-building skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized with the ability to manage multiple searches simultaneously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable operating in fast-paced, ambiguous startup environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Agency recruiting experience is a strong plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Startup recruiting experience is highly preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-starter who takes ownership and moves with urgency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Must be located

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Are you passionate about solving complex challenges in the fintech space? We’re looking for talented individuals to join our dynamic startup, backed by Sequoia Capital. We’re building the universal payment layer to unify all currencies—fiat and crypto—so businesses and consumers can transact seamlessly. If you&#39;re passionate about creating innovative solutions in a dynamic, fast-paced environment, we want to talk to you.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 data-section-id=&quot;1xl63uj&quot; data-start=&quot;0&quot; data-end=&quot;35&quot;&gt;We are hiring a Head of Finance!&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;37&quot; data-end=&quot;332&quot;&gt;As the Head of Finance at Breeze, you’ll build and lead the financial operations that power our growth. This is a highly strategic and operational role focused on financial planning, payments infrastructure, unit economics, and scalable financial systems — not traditional accounting management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;334&quot; data-end=&quot;754&quot;&gt;You’ll partner closely with the CEO and leadership team to drive company-wide financial strategy, improve operational efficiency, and build the financial infrastructure needed to scale a high-growth fintech business. This role is ideal for someone who thrives in fast-paced startup environments, understands the complexity of payments and money movement, and enjoys turning financial data into strategic decision-making.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;756&quot; data-end=&quot;1038&quot;&gt;We’re looking for a finance leader who can operate as both a strategic partner and hands-on builder — someone comfortable diving into payment reconciliations, forecasting growth scenarios, improving financial visibility, and helping shape the operational foundation of the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 data-section-id=&quot;1j5ac4d&quot; data-start=&quot;1040&quot; data-end=&quot;1058&quot;&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul data-start=&quot;1060&quot; data-end=&quot;2647&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;5d58to&quot; data-start=&quot;1060&quot; data-end=&quot;1187&quot;&gt;Own Breeze’s financial operations strategy, building scalable processes that support rapid growth and operational efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;1naztga&quot; data-start=&quot;1188&quot; data-end=&quot;1317&quot;&gt;Lead FP&amp;amp;A across the business, including forecasting, budgeting, scenario modeling, cash flow planning, and headcount planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;1wy5sq9&quot; data-start=&quot;1318&quot; data-end=&quot;1460&quot;&gt;Develop financial models and operational dashboards that provide real-time visibility into company performance, margins, and growth drivers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;1p6toew&quot; data-start=&quot;1461&quot; data-end=&quot;1596&quot;&gt;Partner closely with leadership on strategic planning, capital allocation, pricing strategy, and long-term financial decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;1xgp28t&quot; data-start=&quot;1597&quot; data-end=&quot;1739&quot;&gt;Build and optimize payment reconciliation workflows across banking partners, payment processors, fiat/crypto flows, and treasury operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;hvczpt&quot; data-start=&quot;1740&quot; data-end=&quot;1871&quot;&gt;Analyze transaction flows, payment operations, and revenue streams to improve efficiency, reporting accuracy, and unit economics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;1fdhj3o&quot; data-start=&quot;1872&quot; data-end=&quot;2003&quot;&gt;Drive financial insights across product, operations, partnerships, and go-to-market teams to support data-driven decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;11eaewb&quot; data-start=&quot;2004&quot; data-end=&quot;2114&quot;&gt;Build scalable KPI reporting across revenue, payment volumes, customer performance, and operational metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Are you passionate about solving complex challenges in the fintech space? We’re looking for talented individuals to join our dynamic startup, backed by Sequoia Capital. We’re building the universal payment layer to unify all currencies—fiat and crypto—so businesses and consumers can transact seamlessly. If you&#39;re passionate about creating innovative solutions in a dynamic, fast-paced environment, we want to talk to you.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h1 data-section-id=&quot;1nk1y95&quot; data-start=&quot;391&quot; data-end=&quot;428&quot;&gt;Lead Product Manager – Card Issuing&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;430&quot; data-end=&quot;784&quot;&gt;We’re looking for a &lt;strong data-start=&quot;450&quot; data-end=&quot;489&quot;&gt;Lead Product Manager – Card Issuing&lt;/strong&gt; to build and scale our card issuing platform from &lt;strong data-start=&quot;540&quot; data-end=&quot;547&quot;&gt;0→1&lt;/strong&gt;. This is a highly strategic and execution-driven role responsible for launching and evolving our card program, working across banking partners, payment networks, processors, and internal teams to deliver a best-in-class card experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;786&quot; data-end=&quot;1165&quot;&gt;You’ll own the &lt;strong data-start=&quot;801&quot; data-end=&quot;863&quot;&gt;end-to-end product strategy and execution for card issuing&lt;/strong&gt;, from infrastructure and program setup to consumer-facing experiences and card lifecycle management. This role is ideal for a product leader who has &lt;strong data-start=&quot;1013&quot; data-end=&quot;1059&quot;&gt;successfully launched card programs before&lt;/strong&gt;, understands the complexities of payments infrastructure, and thrives in fast-paced fintech environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1167&quot; data-end=&quot;1385&quot;&gt;If you’ve built card issuing products at a &lt;strong data-start=&quot;1210&quot; data-end=&quot;1258&quot;&gt;leading fintech, neobank, or crypto platform&lt;/strong&gt;, and enjoy solving complex financial infrastructure problems while delivering elegant consumer experiences, we’d love to talk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr data-start=&quot;1387&quot; data-end=&quot;1390&quot;&gt;
